@@bSouthern Tidal Flat, Middle Stretch@@N~
@@lThe tidal flat opens here into its widest section, a broad expanse of grey-tan sand that dries unevenly and catches foot traffic with sudden soft patches.@@N The surface alternates between firm crust and loose wet clay in a pattern that experienced travellers learn to read by colour — the paler sections are dry and walkable, the darker patches are wetter than they appear. @@bSmall transparent crabs dart between burrow mouths at the margins, vanishing when approached.@@N The flat ends to the east where the ground begins to rise toward harder sand and eventually the approach road to the gate. Three long-dead camel carcasses lie in varying stages of decay along the eastern edge, the bones still locked in position as if the animals sat down and refused to continue.
