harbor chain~
@@lThe harbor chain is a serious engineering achievement — iron links each the size of a grown person's forearm, connected to a winch house at the southern harbor arm and to a fixed anchor at the Signal Tower base. The chain is raised at dawn and lowered at dusk, and the raising is announced by a single long tone from the signal tower. Ships in the cove must be fully moored before the chain descends.@@N
