#14307
@@lHarbor Healer's Station@@N~
@@lThe Harbor Healer's Station is a triage room built into the harbor front's southern face, its coral-lime walls maintaining the cool temperature that helps stabilise injured dockworkers during the initial treatment period.@@N Bundles of dried coastal herbs hang from the ceiling above the treatment tables — plant medicines sourced from the tidal flat margins north of the city, used in poultices and infusions that the Harbor Healer has found effective for the particular injuries that dock work produces. @@lThe treatment tables are built wide and low to accommodate workers being brought in on cargo boards.@@N The Station operates continuously during harbor hours and maintains overnight watch for marine injuries and hypothermic incidents. The Harbor Healer is a fixture of the dock district, known to every regular worker, and respected for a medical practice that covers both standard injuries and the stranger conditions that arise from contact with relic-class cargo that has leaked containment.
