@@lNorth Pier, Cargo Loading@@N~
@@lThe North Pier's cargo loading section is the primary commercial entry point for eastbound goods leaving Mafdet by sea — a wide timber-on-stone platform extending over the water with crane fixtures at regular intervals.@@N The pier surface is rough with anti-slip scoring and salt crystal accumulation, and the boards flex slightly underfoot in the sections where the timber is aging. @@lThe Strand Folk basalt visible at the waterline on the pier supports is noticeably smoother than the timber above it — the original foundation, still bearing the Strand Folk construction marks that Littoral Branch archivists date to the period before the Shoreward Compact's formalisation.@@N Cargo is loaded here by teams of four using crane fixtures — a loading method efficient enough that a standard caravan load can be transferred to a vessel in a single working shift.
