@@lHarbormaster's Office@@N~
@@lThe Harbormaster's Office is the operational command centre of Mafdet's harbor — a wide interior room whose north and east walls are covered entirely in the Harbor Register, a continuously maintained record of every vessel, berth, cargo, and commercial interaction in the cove.@@N The Register itself is a living document: clerks update it in real time from pier reports delivered on runners, and the Harbormaster reads the current state by walking the length of the wall, each section representing a specific aspect of harbour operations. @@lBerth assignment boards, weather logs, chain schedule records, and the Quay Concord's commercial traffic register all feed into the Harbormaster's synthesis.@@N The Harbormaster's personal judgment about harbor priorities — which vessels get early berth access, which cargo inspections get expedited, which disputes between ship captains and dock operators get formal resolution — shapes the commercial flow of the entire port. @@lThe office windows face both the harbor front and the cove, allowing the Harbormaster to maintain visual contact with operations at all times.@@N The Harbor Register on the wall is sufficiently complete that a Ledger Quarter archivist once described it as the single most comprehensive real-time commercial record in the corridor.
