@@lSignal Tower Base@@N~
@@lThe base of the Signal Tower is a wide stone platform built at the harbor front's edge, where the stone of the shore meets the masonry of the tower foundation.@@N The tower rises from a basalt plinth that carries the Littoral Branch construction marks of the original builders — this was the first permanent structure built at Mafdet's location, a coastal observation post that predates the city itself. @@lGlass-enclosed lantern panels on the tower face are visible at each gallery level, their coloured glass inserts stored in racks at the base and swapped by signal operators to compose the messages the tower transmits.@@N The lantern rotation schedule is posted at the base: signal codes for standard harbor operations, emergency codes for chain failure or vessel distress, and the daily timing sequence that synchronizes harbor operations from dawn through dusk. Stairs ascend through the tower's interior to the upper galleries and the crown lantern.
