@@lSignal Tower Crown@@N~
@@lThe Signal Tower Crown offers the most comprehensive view of Mafdet's harbor that any fixed position provides — the complete cove basin visible in every direction, the harbor chain's full arc, the breakwater causeway extending east into the harbor mouth, and the Tidewall's seaward face reflecting morning light.@@N @@lTo the north, the North Pier arms extend into the cove, their crane fixtures visible as angular shapes above the pier level.@@N To the south, the South Pier and the Tidewall walk curve away toward the seaward perimeter. The breakwater causeway is visible as a narrow stone line running east from the harbor front toward the deep water. @@lThe Shrine Terrace is visible on the upper city's basalt rise to the northwest — the claw-marked spire at its centre is the highest point visible from the tower.@@N The chain attachment points are clearly visible from this height: the northern anchor at the pier terminal and the winch house position on the southern harbor arm. The chain's current state — raised — is confirmed by its visible arc above the water's surface. The sea beyond the chain is open, and at least two vessels are visible on the outer approach: one inbound, one holding position outside the chain's range.
