@@lThe harbor front curves south here, the geometry of the natural cove pulling the stone promenade away from the straight line of the northern arm and into a gradual southward arc.@@N The curve is the natural result of the cove's asymmetric shape — the southern arm is longer and more gradually inclined than the northern, creating a harbor that curves rather than squares. @@lThe Storm Ledger's bonded cargo piers are visible on the southern arm; the Tidewall begins its distinctive profile further south.@@N The light is different on the southern curve — the prevailing wind comes from the east here rather than the northeast, and the sea spray reaches the promenade more consistently.
