#14329
@@lCaptain's Register Hall@@N~
@@lThe Captain's Register Hall is the Quay Concord's formal administrative presence in the harbor district — a spacious interior room that maintains the Concord's parallel record to the Harbor Register, tracking every vessel operating in the cove from the ship captain's perspective rather than the Harbormaster's.@@N The two registers together create the complete commercial record of the harbor: the Harbormaster's version emphasises cargo throughput and berth management; the Concord's version emphasises vessel status, captain accountability, and maritime contract terms. @@lWhere the two registers disagree, the dispute goes to the Shoreward House for resolution.@@N The hall's interior is calmer than the harbor front outside — ship captains come here to negotiate cargo terms, review the Concord's dispute resolution records, and register new commercial arrangements with the harbor authority. @@lNautical charts cover the eastern wall, including the most recent depth soundings of the approach channel and a detailed map of the harbor basin's current configuration.@@N The Quay Concord's standing charter is displayed near the entrance: a statement of the Concord's purpose that doubles as a statement of the principles that distinguish professional maritime operators from casual ones.
