@@lSouth Pier, Bonded Cargo@@N~
@@lThe South Pier is the Storm Ledger's operational home in the harbor district — the section of pier where high-value, weather-risk-bonded cargo is held between the Ledger Quarter's Storm Ledger Vault and the vessels that will carry it to its destination.@@N The pier surface is cleaner than the North Pier — less casual cargo movement, more formalised handling — and the Storm Ledger's authentication marks appear on the pier posts, the cargo crane housings, and the mooring ring plates. @@yThe bonded cargo held here is among the highest-value material that moves through Mafdet: relic-adjacent goods, precious metals, and high-grade commodities whose maritime insurance requires both Storm Ledger custody and Compact authentication.@@N The Harbor Wardens maintain two permanent inspectors on the South Pier even when no cargo movement is underway. The pier extends east toward the southern breakwater, where the chain's southern anchor point is visible.
