@@lSouth Pier, Chain Terminal@@N~
@@lThe chain terminal marks the south pier's furthest operational reach — the fixed anchor point for the harbor chain's southern end, from which the chain sweeps north across the cove mouth to the Signal Tower's base.@@N The anchor fitting is a massive bronze casting set into the pier's terminal post, with a manual release mechanism that allows the chain to be disconnected in emergency situations. @@lThe chain itself, when raised, creates an arc of iron that appears deceptively lightweight at this distance but represents a barrier that no unassisted vessel can pass.@@N Storm damage patching is visible on the pier boards here — the terminal position takes the brunt of weather that enters the cove mouth before the chain is raised.
