@@lSouth Pier, End Berth@@N~
@@lThe southernmost berth on the South Pier is the Storm Ledger's most secure mooring position — the single berth that the Harbor Wardens can completely isolate from the rest of the pier with a heavy chain across the pier's width.@@N Vessels carrying Class Two or Class Three cargo hold here rather than in the main pier section, their cargoes remaining aboard until Quarantine Ledger clearance is received. @@lThe berth is frequently occupied; the volume of potentially hazardous cargo passing through Mafdet has increased over the past two seasons, driven by the same factors that have increased Quarantine Ledger business.@@N From the end berth, the view east takes in the full open sea beyond the harbor chain.
