#14337
@@lHarbor Chain Winch House@@N~
@@lThe Winch House is the mechanical heart of the harbor — the building that houses the gear system that raises and lowers the harbor chain, and the heavy bronze counterweights that make the chain's daily cycle manageable by a crew of four rather than requiring a dozen.@@N The mechanism itself is visible through the interior — the drive shaft, the gear reduction system, the cable drum, and the chains that connect the mechanism to the chain link that runs to the harbor ring. @@lThe Winch House smells strongly of machine oil and hot metal; the mechanism runs at a specific temperature range, and deviations from this range are the first indicator of mechanical stress that could compromise the chain's reliability.@@N The chain's daily raising is a precision operation — too fast and the chain whips in a way that can damage vessels in its path; too slow and the harbor's commercial timing is disrupted. The Winch Master who manages this operation is one of the most technically experienced people in the harbor.
