@@lThe sailors' quarter is the informal zone south of the main harbor front where off-duty crew members from moored vessels spend their time — a cluster of drinking establishments, food vendors, and makeshift entertainment options that have built up organically around the working harbor.@@N The establishments here operate without Compact certification and with the pragmatic understanding that sailors on shore leave have specific needs that formal commercial licensing does not accommodate well. @@lThe Harbor Wardens tolerate the quarter as long as it stays within its understood boundaries; incidents that spill north into the commercial zone receive a different response.@@N The noise here is louder and less organised than the harbor front proper — competing music, shouted conversations, and the particular sound of a brawl being resolved by its participants rather than by authority.
