navigation song tablets~
@@gThe navigation songs on the wall tablets use a three-part structure: the approach sequence (tidal height and bearing markers from open water), the landmark sequence (visible features in order of appearance), and the caution sequence (seasonal hazards and their indicators). Each tablet covers one approach to one coastal landmark, and the alcove contains tablets for more than forty approach lines along the coast in both directions from Mafdet. The oldest tablets predate the Strandline Compact's chartering of the harbor; the newest are dated to within living memory, added when a new hazard was confirmed and documented.@@N
~
E
guardian origin stories~
@@gThe guardian origin stories kept on the lower shelf are not a single narrative but parallel accounts from different Strand Folk communities, all describing the same event: the appearance of a feline form at a coastline where no such animal should exist, followed by a period of protected fishing and safe passage that ended when a specific oath was broken. The accounts differ in detail but agree on the mechanism — the guardian appeared, made an agreement, and departed when the agreement was violated. The Strand Rememberers treat these as historical records, not theology.@@N
