@@yThe Shrine Terrace@@N~
@@yThe Shrine Terrace is a broad basalt platform elevated above the city's roofline, offering unobstructed views in all directions: the harbor and breakwater to the east, the Ledger Quarter's archive rooflines to the west, the Tidewall's defensive profile to the south, and the Tidemouth Dunes at the edge of visibility to the northwest.@@N The claw-marked spire at the terrace's center is the tallest structure in Mafdet — a column of polished black basalt rising to a height visible from the outer harbor approach, its top carved with the four-groove claw mark in monumental scale. @@yThe claw iconography of the Shrine of the First Claw covers the terrace pavement in a continuous floor mosaic: four-groove claw marks oriented toward each cardinal direction, forming a pattern that reads as a jurisdictional claim over all of Mafdet's commercial and judicial space.@@N The verdict boards on the terrace's western face display the Swift Court's most recent judgments — decisions rendered in open session are transcribed to wax-sealed tablets and mounted here for a standard holding period. @@yThe terrace functions as Mafdet's highest-authority judicial space: any oath spoken here is binding under all three of the city's legal traditions — the Compact's commercial law, the Littoral Branch's maritime precedent, and the guardian cult's oath-enforcement tradition.@@N
