claw iconography~
@@yThe claw marks in the floor mosaic follow a precise format: four parallel grooves, each exactly the width of a large feline pad-bone, spaced as they would appear in the impression of a living paw. The grooves in the central spire are of the same proportions but enlarged to monumental scale. The mosaic uses a different stone for each groove — dark basalt for the outer grooves, pale limestone for the inner ones — creating a visual rhythm that is visible from the harbor below on clear days.@@N
~
E
verdict boards~
@@yThe verdict boards carry tablets spanning the last seasonal cycle of Swift Court decisions: commercial disputes between Ledger Houses, oath-breach findings against identified parties, and jurisdictional boundary rulings clarifying where Compact authority ends and maritime custom begins. Each tablet lists the parties, the finding, and the assigned consequence — consequences range from commercial penalties in Saltweight-certified amounts to the Guardian-Judicial sanction of public oath-requirement, in which a party must ascend to the terrace and speak a binding oath in full view of the harbor. Several current tablets bear the Quarantine Ledger's referral mark, indicating the Swift Court has been asked to rule on classification disputes that the Ledger cannot resolve through administrative means.@@N
