@@RSwift Court of the First Claw@@N~
@@RThe Swift Court of the First Claw is the Shrine Terrace's formal judicial space — an open court ringed by carved stone benches, with a raised judgment stone at the western end where the Shrine's adjudicator stands to deliver verdicts.@@N The court is named for the speed of guardian-tradition justice: no case continues beyond three sessions, and the verdict on any commercial dispute must be delivered before the involved parties' ships are delayed by the unresolved debt. @@RThe judgment stone is a block of unpolished basalt, deliberately left rough in contrast to the polished pavement of the terrace — the rough stone is said to prevent anyone standing on it from speaking anything but the truth, a practical belief maintained by the guardian cult's accumulated authority over oath-taking.@@N The observation gallery above the court's northern wall allows witnesses and interested parties to observe without participating in the floor's formal proceedings. @@RThe carved verdict tablets on the court's display boards represent decisions rendered here, each one a piece of the Shrine's ongoing documentary claim to judicial jurisdiction over commercial Mafdet.@@N
