@@RThe Oath Chamber@@N~
@@RThe Oath Chamber is the interior space of the Shrine of the First Claw — a low-ceilinged hall cut from the basalt spire's base, lit by oil lamps whose flame behavior is considered an indicator of oath sincerity.@@N The First Claw sculpture at the chamber's center is not a representation of the guardian but a preserved record of a physical impression: a worn basalt block bearing four parallel claw marks pressed into its upper surface at a depth inconsistent with any tool in the Compact's documented inventory. @@RThe claw marks on the sculpture are the definitional reference for all guardian iconography in Mafdet — the four-groove motif in the floor mosaics, the wall carvings on the terrace approach, and the stamp on commercial oaths all derive their proportions from measurements taken from this block.@@N The oath-sealing ritual performed here requires the oath-taker to press one hand into the claw impression while speaking the oath aloud — a physical contact requirement that the Shrine adjudicators enforce strictly. @@RThe lamps in this chamber use a specific oil compound burning with a blue-orange flame that the Strand Rememberers identify as consistent with a coastal kelp-extract used in their oldest fire-making tradition.@@N
