claw marks~
@@RThe claw marks in the basalt block are examined by Shrine adjudicators before every formal oath ceremony. The marks show no signs of tool work: no chipping along the groove edges, no entry angle consistent with chisel or gouge, and a depth profile that increases toward the groove's center in a way that matches biological pressure rather than mechanical cutting. The groove surfaces are polished from centuries of contact with oath-takers' hands, the basalt worn to a different texture than the surrounding stone surface.@@N
