oath-sealing ritual~
@@RThe ritual's requirements are: the oath-taker speaks the obligation aloud in the Compact's formal legal language; places one hand flat against the claw impression block; repeats the obligation in the guardian cult's older invocation formula taught by Shrine adjudicators immediately before the ceremony; and waits for the adjudicator's confirmation. The Shrine maintains that an oath spoken here is binding regardless of any party's belief in the guardian tradition — the binding derives from the public testimony element, not from supernatural enforcement, though the Shrine does not discourage belief in the latter.@@N
