@@gTerrace Garden, Eastern Side@@N~
@@gThe eastern garden area of the Shrine Terrace is a maintained border of coastal plants set into raised stone beds along the terrace's eastern edge — species from the tidal zone, selected for their tolerance of the salt spray that reaches this height from the harbor below.@@N @@lThe garden was established by a Strand Rememberer practitioner who served the Shrine three generations ago, the planting serving as a living demonstration of coastal botanical knowledge alongside the Shrine's documentary traditions.@@N The beds are maintained by Shrine practitioners on a rotation, the work considered a form of contemplative practice rather than maintenance labor.
~
