#14397
@@lTerrace Overlook, Harbor View@@N~
@@lThe harbor view from the terrace's eastern lookout takes in the full sweep of the commercial port below: the two pier arms extending into the harbor basin, the Signal Tower rising from the harbor's central section, the breakwater causeway extending eastward, and the harbor chain in its raised position spanning the cove mouth.@@N @@gThe height here makes the harbor's geometry legible in a way impossible from harbor level — the crescent shape of the cove, the alignment of the pier arms with the prevailing current direction, and the signal tower's placement at the junction of the harbor's navigation axes are all visible as intentional design.@@N @@lAt dawn, when the harbor chain is lowered to allow the day's first ships to enter, the sound of the chain mechanism carries even to this height as a sequence of deep tonal impacts.@@N
