#14398
@@yTerrace Overlook, Western Extension@@N~
@@yThe western extension of the terrace overlook area provides a supplementary vantage point over the Ledger Quarter below — the archive rooflines are visible as a compressed pattern of thick-walled structures, fire-resistant construction identifiable by the absence of upper-story windows and the presence of sealed roof hatches rather than open terraces.@@N @@gThe Carter's Way is visible as a pale dust-line running through the commercial district from the Landward Gate approach eastward toward the harbor district.@@N The Saltglass Reach is visible at the western horizon on clear days — a pale glint of mineral surface at the edge of the dunes, the territorial boundary between Reach and city marked by the transition from the Reach's salt-flat terrain to the Tidemouth Dunes' brackish scrub zone.
~
