#14399
@@gTerrace Overlook, Reach View@@N~
@@gThe Reach View overlook faces northwest from the Shrine Terrace's highest accessible point, the sightline running over the Tidemouth Dunes and into the Saltglass Reach — on exceptionally clear days, the Reach's surface glints with the mineral light that gives it its name.@@N @@bThe Tidemouth Dunes are visible as a tawny band between the city's western wall and the pale mineral expanse of the Reach beyond, the approach path threading through them invisible at this distance but knowable by the gaps between dune crests where the trail runs.@@N The Reach View overlook is a traditional first stop for arriving caravaneers who reach the Shrine Terrace — standing here and looking back over the route taken is a recognized completion ritual for Glasswalk Guides and Reach Wardens who have finished an escort.
~
